<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-0702 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author describes the activities of the EEC Commission for the definitionand implementation of an EEC-wide environmental policy and highlightsthe environmental dimension in all national and EEC policies. Actionsand measures of air pollution control are taken to demonstrate specialproblems which may arise from particular national interests and whichcall for an integration as comprehensive as possible. The part playedby technology is underlined as an indispensable element in the protectionof the environment. An outlook on further air pollution control measuresplanned for the future is given.</TEXT></DOC>